cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.ST, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper presents a novel algorithm for piecewise linear regression, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The algorithm is based on partitioning the data and learning a linear model in each partition, which is similar in spirit to k-means clustering algorithm. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.ST (Statistics). Additionally, the paper involves data analysis and modeling, which suggests the sub-categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as possible options.
